It photosynthesizes while it’s alive.

It eventually falls.

It decomposes.

Then, years later, its nutrients quietly feed a conversation that never knew its name.

Maybe that’s why your “Money Bin” has always felt different to me than a notebook.

It’s less an archive than a forest floor.

Not a place where ideas are frozen.

A place where old growth becomes new growth.

